Spring security

Spring security provide application level security like 
- login and logout functionality 
- Allow / Block access to URL’s to logged in users
- Allow / Block access to URL’s to logged in users And with certain roles.

What it provides ?
- Username and password authentication
- SSO / Okta / LDAP
- Application level Authorisation 
- Intra App Authorisation like OAuth
- Microservice security (Using tokens , JWT)
- Method level security 





Type of authentication

Basic Authentication -> Basic Authentication is a method for an HTTP user agent (e.g., a web browser) to provide a username and password when making a request. When employing Basic Authentication, users include an encoded string in the Authorization header of each request they make.

Bearer token authentication -> The bearer token is a cryptic string, usually generated by the server in response to a login request.


Session Id Authentication -> Reference token 
	
	
JWT -> Json web token  -> Value token 